The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves designing algorithms to optimize social welfare, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of worst-case analysis, which is a common technique in theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper focuses on matching markets, which is a subfield of market algorithms (cs.MA).
